                                    figsize=(14,8),
                                    title="Distribution of Deaths by District")

Comparing those two pie charts indicate that the proportion of deaths and the proportion of the population are similar. This means that districts with higher population density normally will have more deaths compared to other districts.

In conclusion, the digital infrastructure and urban planning for the city of Barcelona has to be revisited. We need to equally contribute to the worse off districts, form more superblocks, and implement stricter traffic regulations in the areas where high accident rates and car traffic are evident. This would raise the standard of living as citizens and residents will have more walking space as well as better air quality. In addition, traffic police nned to be deployed in certain areas and be on high alert during the specified months of the year when traffic is at its highest. Finally, we need to invest in public transportation in the areas where we'll implement those policies in order to make up for the lessened traffic and to also increase efficiency by offering more space and reduce our carbon footprint.
